116 162 float GCCPhaT::estimateAngle(float timeDelayX1, float timeDelayX2,
117 float timeDelayY1, float timeDelayY2) {
118 // Calculate average time delays on each axis.
119 162 float avgTimeDelayX_s = (timeDelayX1 + timeDelayX2) / 2.0;
120 162 float avgTimeDelayY_s = (timeDelayY1 + timeDelayY2) / 2.0;
121
122 // Normalize average time by distange betweeen mics (equivalently max time
123 // delay) since microphone array are not in a perfect square.
124 162 float dx = avgTimeDelayX_s / MAX_DELAY_MIC1_2;
125 162 float dy = avgTimeDelayY_s / MAX_DELAY_MIC2_3;
126
127 // Compute angle and transform to correct coordinate system (FR5.3). We get
128 // the below equation since:
129 162 float angle = std::atan2(dy, dx);
130
131 // Rotate pi/2 counterclock wise so that angle of 0 faces towards the front of
132 // the glasses frame.
133 162 angle -= PI_32 / 2.0;
134
135 // Convert angle to be in range of 0 and 2pi.
136 162 angle = normalizeAngleRad(angle);
137
138 162 return angle;
139 }
